The paper deals with economic mechanisms and auctions, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The use of multi-dimensional bids and the need for robustness suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and algorithmic game theory (cs.EC). The technical aspects of establishing equilibrium existence and bid structures suggest a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
